𝗛𝗔𝗟𝗙/𝗔𝗡𝗚𝗘𝗟 𝗔𝗟𝗕𝗨𝗠 𝗙𝗨𝗡𝗗𝗥𝗔𝗜𝗦𝗘𝗥 | 𝗦𝗔𝗡 𝗙𝗥𝗔𝗡, 𝗡𝗢𝗩𝗘𝗠𝗕𝗘𝗥 𝟮𝟳𝗧𝗛 | 𝘄/ 𝗠𝗬𝗦𝗧𝗘𝗥𝗬 𝗪𝗔𝗜𝗧𝗥𝗘𝗦𝗦, 𝗞𝗜𝗡𝗗𝗘𝗞𝗘𝗟 𝗜𝗜 & 𝗘𝗟𝗟𝗬 𝗠𝗔𝗘
$12.50 𝗘𝗔𝗥𝗟𝗬 𝗔𝗖𝗖𝗘𝗦𝗦 𝗣𝗥𝗘𝗦𝗔𝗟𝗘 𝗣𝗔𝗦𝗦𝗪𝗢𝗥𝗗: GOOSEANGEL333 (NOW SOLD OUT)—ALL GENERAL ADMISSION TICKETS ON SALE @ 5:00PM NZT
It’s not often a band as exciting as Half/Angel emerges in Te Whanganui-a-Tara. Less than a year since their inception, their name has become a whispered promise across the city’s music scene, with many already declaring them next in line to the throne. Now, at the height of their powers, they’re channeling the raw energy that’s made them a household name into a one-night-only performance at San Fran on November 27th.
Half/Angel and Goose Garden are delighted to present a supporting lineup woven from their favourite voices in the scene. A standout among them is 𝗠𝗬𝗦𝗧𝗘𝗥𝗬 𝗪𝗔𝗜𝗧𝗥𝗘𝗦𝗦, who conjured one of Aotearoa’s most enchanting indie releases of 2024 with Bright Black Night. We’re also delighted to invite 𝗘𝗟𝗟𝗬 𝗠𝗔𝗘, who left audiences bewitched when she first unveiled her atmospheric folk on Te Whanganui-a-Tara stages last year. And if, in any world, this lineup wasn’t already something out of a dream, we’ve invited the effervescent 𝗞𝗜𝗡𝗗𝗘𝗞𝗘𝗟 𝗜𝗜 to keep your feet moving ‘til close.
We’ve released a small number of heavily discounted tickets, you can access these by using the password GOOSEANGEL333. Link in bio. Don’t walk, run
